---
import StickySidebarLayout from './StickySidebarLayout.astro';
---

<StickySidebarLayout title="Sticky Sidebar Layout Example">
	<div slot="main">
		<h1>Article Title</h1>
		<p>This is an example of how to use the Sticky Sidebar layout. The sidebar will remain visible as you scroll through this content.</p>
		
		<h2>Introduction</h2>
		<p>This layout is perfect for articles, documentation, or any content that benefits from persistent sidebar navigation or information.</p>
		<p>The sidebar uses <code>position: sticky</code> to remain in view while the main content scrolls naturally.</p>
		
		<h2>Features</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Responsive design that stacks on mobile</li>
			<li>Sticky positioning that works across browsers</li>
			<li>Customizable content slots</li>
			<li>Clean, minimal styling</li>
		</ul>
		
		<h2>Usage</h2>
		<p>Simply import the StickySidebarLayout component and use the "main" and "sidebar" slots to add your content.</p>
		<p>The layout automatically handles the responsive behavior and sticky positioning.</p>
		
		<h2>Customization</h2>
		<p>The layout uses CSS custom properties and can be easily customized by overriding the styles.</p>
		<p>The pink background and border styling are just examples - change them to match your design system.</p>
		
		<h2>More Content</h2>
		<p>Keep scrolling to see how the sidebar stays in position while this content flows naturally.</p>
		<p>This makes it perfect for table of contents, author information, related links, or any persistent navigation.</p>
	</div>
	<div slot="sidebar">
		<h3>Navigation</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="#intro">Introduction</a></li>
			<li><a href="#features">Features</a></li>
			<li><a href="#usage">Usage</a></li>
			<li><a href="#customization">Customization</a></li>
		</ul>
		
		<h3>Quick Links</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></li>
			<li><a href="#bottom">Jump to Bottom</a></li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</StickySidebarLayout>

<style>
	ul {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
	}
	
	li {
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}
	
	a {
		color: #333;
		text-decoration: none;
		padding: 4px 8px;
		border-radius: 4px;
		display: block;
	}
	
	a:hover {
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
	
	h3 {
		margin-bottom: 12px;
		margin-top: 20px;
	}
	
	h3:first-child {
		margin-top: 0;
	}
	
	code {
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
		padding: 2px 6px;
		border-radius: 3px;
		font-family: 'Monaco', 'Courier New', monospace;
	}
</style>